#. type: Content of: <section><title>
#: en/content/features/video-calls.xml:6
msgid "Video and Audio Calls"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/video-calls.xml:11
msgid ""
"The video and audio calls feature of the <emphasis role=\"bold\">OTRS "
"Business Solution</emphasis>™ provides real-time calls between two users "
"right from the comfort of the OTRS frontend. The calls will be provided over "
"a direct peer-to-peer connection established between two users, where "
"possible. This feature depends heavily on the chat, which must be active for "
"video and audio calls to be possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/features/video-calls.xml:15
msgid ""
"Video and audio calls are based on a quite young technology called WebRTC. "
"The implementation of WebRTC APIs in modern browsers is an ongoing effort. "
"Currently, OTRS video and audio calls are supported only in the latest "
"versions of Mozilla Firefox and Google Chrome (for Chrome a <link linkend="
"\"chrome-ssl-required\">HTTPS Enabled Web Server</link> is required)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/features/video-calls.xml:23
msgid ""
"The following system configuration options are relevant for this feature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/features/video-calls.xml:30
msgid ""
"Controls whether or not the video and audio calling feature is enabled. "
"Please note that the same switch will control <link linkend=\"chat\">the "
"chat</link> feature too."
msgstr ""

